Privacy Policy for Nawalah

Last updated: 17-07-2024

1. Introduction

Welcome to Nawalah ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and providing a safe, secure experience for all users of our mobile application ("App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our App.

By using Nawalah, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our App.

2. Information We Collect

We collect several types of information from and about users of our App, including:

a. Personal Information:
- Name
- Email address
- Phone number
- Payment information
- Address (for delivery purposes)

b. Usage Data:
- Location data (with your consent)
- App usage statistics
- Device information (e.g., device ID, operating system)

c. Transaction Data:
- Items purchased or donated
- Transaction history

3. How We Collect Information

a. Directly from you when you:
- Create an account
- Use our services
- Contact our customer support

b. Automatically as you navigate through the App:
- Usage details
- Location data (if permitted)

c. From third parties, such as our business partners and service providers.

4. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect to:

a. Provide, maintain, and improve our App and services
b. Process transactions and manage your account
c. Facilitate food donations and connect donors with recipients
d. Communicate with you about our services, promotions, and updates
e. Respond to your comments, questions, and customer service requests
f. Monitor and analyze usage trends and preferences
g. Protect the security and integrity of our App
h. Comply with legal obligations

5. Disclosure of Your Information

We may disclose your personal information to:

a. Service providers and business partners who assist us in operating our App and conducting our business
b. NGOs and charitable organizations to facilitate food donations
c. Law enforcement or other governmental agencies in response to a legal request or when required by law
d. Protect our rights, property, or safety, and that of our users or others

We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties for their marketing purposes.

6. Data Security

We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

7. Your Rights and Choices

You have the right to:

a. Access, update, or delete your personal information
b. Object to the processing of your personal information
c. Request restrictions on the use of your personal information
d. Data portability
e. Withdraw consent (where applicable)

To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information provided in the "Contact Us" section.

8. Children's Privacy

Our App is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe we may have collected information about a child, please contact us.

9. Changes to Our Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.

10. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our practices, please contact us at:

Nawalah
Email: info@nawalahapp.com


11. Consent

By using our App, you consent to our Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.
